Serves_5:
{
    "recipeSource": "My Kitchen",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-09-01",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Wash and soak 2 cups of basmati rice in water for 30 minutes. Chop 2 onions, 2 tomatoes, 2 green chillies, and 1 cup of mixed vegetables (carrots, peas, beans, etc.). Grind 1 inch ginger, 4 garlic cloves, and 1/2 cup of fresh coriander leaves into a paste.",
            "time": 30,
            "tool": "bowl, knife, cutting board, blender"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking Rice",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "In a large pot, bring 8 cups of water to a boil. Add 1 tsp of salt and the soaked rice. Cook for 8-10 minutes or until the rice is 80% cooked. Drain the water and set aside.",
            "time": 15,
            "tool": "pot, strainer"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking Vegetables",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "In a separate pot, heat 2 tbsp of oil. Add the chopped onions and saut√© until golden brown. Add the ginger-garlic-coriander paste and saut√© for 2 minutes. Add the chopped tomatoes and green chillies and cook until the tomatoes are soft. Add the mixed vegetables and cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 tsp of salt, 1 tsp of red chilli powder, 1 tsp of garam masala, and 1 tsp of biryani masala. Mix well.",
            "time": 20,
            "tool": "pot, spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Layering",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "In a large pot, spread a layer of the cooked rice. Add a layer of the cooked vegetables on top. Repeat the layers until all the rice and vegetables are used up. Cover the pot with a tight-fitting lid and cook on low heat for 10-15 minutes.",
            "time": 15,
            "tool": "pot, spoon, lid"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 5,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Garnish with fried onions and fresh coriander leaves. Serve hot with raita and papad.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "plate, spoon"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "recipeSource": "Food Network",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-09-15",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Meanwhile, cut 4 boneless, skinless chicken breasts into bite-sized pieces. Season with salt and pepper. Mince 4 cloves of garlic and chop 1/4 cup of fresh parsley.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "large pot, knife, cutting board"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add 1 pound of pasta to the boiling water and cook according to package instructions until al dente. While the pasta is cooking, heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, about 5-7 minutes. Remove the chicken from the skillet and set aside.",
            "time": 20,
            "tool": "large skillet, tongs"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Sauce",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "In the same skillet, add 2 tablespoons of butter and melt over medium heat. Add the minced garlic and cook for 1-2 minutes until fragrant. Add 1 cup of chicken broth and bring to a simmer. Add 1/2 cup of heavy cream and stir to combine. Simmer for 5-7 minutes until the sauce has thickened slightly.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "skillet, whisk"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Combining",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add the cooked pasta to the skillet with the sauce and toss to coat. Add the cooked chicken and chopped parsley and toss again. Serve hot.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "skillet, tongs"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 5,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Divide the chicken pasta among 5 plates and serve immediately.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "plates"
        }
    ]
}

        {

            "stageTitle": "Pasta Dough",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "In a mixing bowl, combine 3 cups of all-purpose flour, 1 teaspoon of salt, and 4 eggs. Mix well until the dough forms. Knead the dough for 10 minutes until it becomes smooth and elastic. Cover the dough with a damp cloth and let it rest for 30 minutes.",
            "time": 45,
            "tool": "mixing bowl"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Rolling the Dough",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Divide the dough into 4 equal parts. Roll out each part into a thin sheet using a rolling pin or a pasta machine. Cut the sheet into 3-inch circles using a cookie cutter or a glass.",
            "time": 30,

        },
        {

        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 6,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking the Pasta",

        },
        {

        }
    ]

{
    "recipeSource": "Bon App√©tit",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-09-01",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Finely chop 1 onion, 2 garlic cloves, and 1 carrot. Mince 2 sprigs of fresh rosemary. Grate 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese.",
            "time": 15,
            "tool": "Knife, cutting board, grater"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the chopped onion, garlic, and carrot. Cook for 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are softened. Add 1 pound of ground beef and cook for 8-10 minutes, breaking up the meat with a wooden spoon, until browned.",
            "time": 20,
            "tool": "Large skillet, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Simmering",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add 1/2 cup of dry red wine and cook for 2-3 minutes, until the wine has mostly evaporated. Add 1 can (28 ounces) of crushed tomatoes, 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and the minced rosemary. Bring to a simmer and cook for 15-20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the sauce has thickened.",
            "time": 25,
            "tool": "Large skillet, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Serve the bolognese over cooked pasta, topped with grated Parmesan cheese.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "Serving dish, pasta pot, colander"
        }
    ]
}

            "tool": "knife, cutting board, grater"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",

            "instruction": "Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the chopped onion, garlic, and carrot.             "time": 20,
            "tool": "large skillet, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Simmering",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add 1/2 cup of dry red wine and cook for 2-3 minutes, until the wine has mostly evaporated.             "time": 25,
            "tool": "wooden spoon"
        },
        {

Serves_3:
{
    "recipeSource": "Allrecipes.com",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-10-15",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Chop 1 onion, 2 cloves of garlic, and 1 red bell pepper. Drain and rinse 1 can of kidney beans and 1 can of black beans. Set aside.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "knife, cutting board, colander"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "In a large pot, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil over medium heat. Add the chopped onion, garlic, and red bell pepper. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "large pot, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add 1 pound of ground beef to the pot. Cook until browned, breaking up any large chunks with a wooden spoon.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "large pot, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add 1 tablespoon of chili powder, 1 teaspoon of cumin, 1 teaspoon of paprika, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt to the pot. Stir to combine.",
            "time": 1,
            "tool": "measuring spoons, large pot, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 5,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add 1 can of diced tomatoes, 1 can of tomato sauce, and the drained and rinsed beans to the pot. Stir to combine.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "can opener, large pot, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 6,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Bring the chili to a simmer. Reduce the heat to low and let it cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
            "time": 20,
            "tool": "large pot, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 7,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Serve the chili hot, topped with shredded cheese, sour cream, and chopped cilantro, if desired.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "bowls, spoons, toppings"
        }
    ]
}

{

    "instructions": [
        {

        {

            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Peel and chop 1 small carrot.",

            "stageTitle": "Preparation",

            "instruction": "Peel and chop 1 small garlic clove.",

        },

            "stageTitle": "Cooking",

            "instruction": "Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",

        },
        {

            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",

        },
        {

            "stageTitle": "Cooking",

            "instruction": "Add the onion, carrot, and garlic and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",

            "tool": "Dutch oven"
        },

            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Stir in 1 tablespoon of tomato paste and cook for 1 minute.",

            "tool": "Dutch oven"
        },

            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add 1/2 cup of red wine and bring to a simmer.",

            "tool": "Dutch oven"
        },
        {

            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add enough beef broth to cover the beef and vegetables.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "Dutch oven"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 12,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Cover the Dutch oven and transfer to the preheated oven.",
            "time": 120,

        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 13,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",

            "instruction": "Serve hot with crusty bread or over mashed potatoes.",

        }
    ]

Serves_2:
{
    "recipeSource": "Allrecipes",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-10-15",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "oven"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Cut the beef into 1-inch cubes. Peel and chop the onions and carrots. Mince the garlic. Chop the bacon.",
            "time": 20,
            "tool": "knife"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "In a large Dutch oven, cook the bacon over medium heat until crisp. Remove with a slotted spoon and set aside. Add the beef to the bacon fat and cook until browned on all sides. Remove with a slotted spoon and set aside.",
            "time": 20,
            "tool": "Dutch oven"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add the onions, carrots, and garlic to the Dutch oven and cook until softened, about 5 minutes. Add the tomato paste and cook for 1 minute. Add the beef broth, red wine, thyme, bay leaves, and reserved bacon and beef. Bring to a simmer.",
            "time": 15,
            "tool": "Dutch oven"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 5,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Cover the Dutch oven and transfer to the preheated oven. Cook for 2 hours, or until the beef is tender.",
            "time": 120,
            "tool": "Dutch oven"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 6,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Remove the bay leaves and serve hot with crusty bread or over mashed potatoes.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "plate"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "recipeSource": "The Spruce Eats",

    "instructions": [
        {

            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Preheat the oven to 350¬∞F (175¬∞C).",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "oven"
        },
        {

            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Cut the beef into 1-inch cubes. Peel and chop the onions and carrots. Mince the garlic. Slice the mushrooms. Tie the thyme and bay leaves together with kitchen twine.",

        },
        {

        {

            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add the onions, carrots, and garlic to the pot and cook until softened, about 5 minutes. Add the tomato paste and cook for 1 minute. Add the beef back to the pot along with the red wine, beef broth, and tied herbs. Bring to a simmer.",

            "tool": "Dutch oven or oven-safe pot, spoon"
        },
        {

        {

            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Remove the pot from the oven and place it on the stovetop. Remove the tied herbs and discard. In a small bowl, mix together the butter and flour to form a paste.         },
        {

        }
    ]

Serves_1:
{
    "recipeSource": "BBC Good Food",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-09-01",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Preheat the oven to 200¬∞C. Season the beef fillet with salt and pepper.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "Oven"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Sealing the Beef",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Heat the oil in a frying pan over high heat. Sear the beef fillet for 30 seconds on each side until browned all over. Remove from the pan and set aside to cool.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "Frying pan"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Preparing the Mushroom Mixture",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "In the same frying pan, melt the butter and add the chopped mushrooms, garlic, and thyme. Cook for 10 minutes until the mushrooms are soft and the liquid has evaporated. Season with salt and pepper.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "Frying pan"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Wrapping the Beef",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Roll out the puff pastry on a floured surface. Spread the mushroom mixture over the pastry, leaving a 2cm border. Place the beef fillet on top of the mushroom mixture. Brush the edges of the pastry with beaten egg. Fold the pastry over the beef, pressing the edges to seal. Trim any excess pastry and brush the top with beaten egg.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "Rolling pin"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 5,
            "stageTitle": "Baking the Beef Wellington",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Place the beef Wellington on a baking tray lined with baking paper. Bake in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes for medium-rare beef. Remove from the oven and let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing and serving.",
            "time": 25,
            "tool": "Oven"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 6,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Serve the beef Wellington with your choice of sides and enjoy!",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "Plate"
        }
    ]
}

Serves_6:
{
    "recipeSource": "BBC Good Food",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-09-01",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Prepare the Beef",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Season the beef fillet with salt and pepper. Heat the oil in a large frying pan over high heat and sear the beef for 1-2 minutes on each side until browned all over. Remove from the pan and set aside to cool.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "frying pan"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Prepare the Mushroom Mixture",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Melt the butter in a frying pan over medium heat. Add the mushrooms and cook for 5-7 minutes until they release their liquid and start to brown. Add the garlic and thyme and cook for another minute. Remove from the heat and set aside to cool.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "frying pan"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Wrap the Beef in Prosciutto",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Lay out a large sheet of cling film and place the prosciutto slices on top, overlapping slightly. Spread the mushroom mixture over the prosciutto. Place the beef fillet in the centre and use the cling film to wrap the prosciutto and mushrooms tightly around the beef. Chill in the fridge for at least 30 minutes.",
            "time": 30,
            "tool": "cling film"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Prepare the Pastry",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Roll out the puff pastry on a lightly floured surface to a rectangle large enough to wrap around the beef. Remove the cling film from the beef and place it in the centre of the pastry. Brush the edges of the pastry with beaten egg and fold the pastry over the beef, pressing the edges together to seal. Trim off any excess pastry and use the trimmings to decorate the top of the Wellington. Chill in the fridge for at least 30 minutes.",
            "time": 30,
            "tool": "rolling pin"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 5,
            "stageTitle": "Cook the Beef Wellington",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Preheat the oven to 200¬∞C/180¬∞C fan/gas 6. Brush the pastry with beaten egg and use a sharp knife to score a criss-cross pattern on top. Bake for 35-40 minutes until the pastry is golden brown and the beef is cooked to your liking. Rest for 10 minutes before slicing and serving.",
            "time": 40,
            "tool": "oven"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 6,
            "stageTitle": "Serve",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Slice the Beef Wellington into thick slices and serve with your choice of vegetables and potatoes.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "knife"
        }
    ]
}

Serves_1:
{
    "recipeSource": "Taste of Home",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-08-25",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Cut 200g of white fish into bite-sized pieces. Peel and chop 1 small onion, 1 garlic clove, and 1 small tomato. Cut 1 small bell pepper into thin strips. Chop 1 tablespoon of fresh cilantro.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "knife, cutting board"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a medium-sized pot over medium heat. Add the chopped onion and garlic and saut√© for 2-3 minutes until softened. Add the chopped tomato and bell pepper and cook for another 2-3 minutes until the vegetables are slightly softened. Add 1/2 cup of water, 1/2 teaspoon of salt, and 1/4 teaspoon of black pepper. Bring to a boil and then reduce the heat to low and let simmer for 5 minutes.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "pot, spatula"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Adding Fish",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add the fish pieces to the pot and gently stir to combine. Cover the pot and let simmer for 5-7 minutes until the fish is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.",
            "time": 7,
            "tool": "pot, spatula"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Garnish with chopped cilantro and serve hot with rice or crusty bread.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "plate, spoon"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "recipeSource": "Thai Kitchen",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-09-01",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Clean and cut 1 kg of fish into bite-sized pieces. Peel and chop 2 onions, 4 garlic cloves, and 2 cm of ginger. Cut 2 red chillies into thin slices. Chop 1 bunch of coriander leaves and keep aside.",
            "time": 20,
            "tool": "knife, cutting board"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Heat 2 tbsp of oil in a pan and add the chopped onions, garlic, and ginger. Fry until the onions turn translucent. Add 2 tbsp of Thai red curry paste and fry for 1 minute. Add 1 can of coconut milk and 1 cup of water. Bring to a boil.",
            "time": 15,
            "tool": "pan"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add the fish pieces and sliced red chillies to the pan. Simmer for 10-15 minutes until the fish is cooked through. Add salt to taste.",
            "time": 15,
            "tool": "pan"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Garnish with chopped coriander leaves and serve hot with steamed rice.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "plate"
        }
    ]
}

Serves_3:
{
    "recipeSource": "Allrecipes",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-09-01",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Clean and cut 1 kg of fish into bite-sized pieces. Peel and chop 3 medium-sized potatoes, 1 onion, and 2 garlic cloves. Cut 2 tomatoes into small pieces. Chop 1 red bell pepper and 1 green bell pepper. Rinse and chop 1 bunch of fresh cilantro.",
            "time": 20,
            "tool": "knife, cutting board"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add the chopped onion and garlic and saut√© for 2-3 minutes until softened. Add the chopped bell peppers and saut√© for another 2-3 minutes. Add the chopped tomatoes and cook for 5 minutes until they start to break down. Add the chopped potatoes and 1 liter of water. Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to low and simmer for 15 minutes until the potatoes are tender.",
            "time": 25,
            "tool": "large pot, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Adding Fish",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add the fish pieces to the pot and gently stir to combine. Simmer for another 5-7 minutes until the fish is cooked through. Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
            "time": 7,
            "tool": "wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Ladle the stew into bowls and sprinkle with chopped cilantro. Serve hot with crusty bread or rice.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "ladle"
        }
    ]
}
Serves_5:
{
    "recipeSource": "Allrecipes",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-08-25",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Clean and cut 1 kg of fish (such as cod, haddock, or sea bass) into bite-sized pieces. Peel and chop 1 onion, 2 garlic cloves, and 2 tomatoes. Slice 2 bell peppers and 2 potatoes. Drain and rinse 1 can of chickpeas.",
            "time": 20,
            "tool": "knife, cutting board, colander"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add the onion and garlic and cook for 2-3 minutes until softened. Add the tomatoes and cook for another 2-3 minutes. Add the bell peppers and potatoes and cook for 5 minutes. Add 1 teaspoon of paprika, 1 bay leaf, and 1 cup of water. Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to low. Simmer for 10 minutes until the vegetables are tender.",
            "time": 20,
            "tool": "large pot, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Adding Fish and Chickpeas",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add the fish and chickpeas to the pot. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Cover and simmer for 5-7 minutes until the fish is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "large pot, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Remove the bay leaf and serve the Portuguese fish stew hot with crusty bread or rice.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "ladle, serving bowls"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "recipeSource": "The Spruce Eats",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-09-20",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Preheat the oven to 180¬∞C. Peel and chop 4 cloves of garlic. Cut 1 lemon into wedges. Remove the leaves from 2 sprigs of rosemary and chop them finely.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "oven, knife, cutting board"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Seasoning",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Rub the lamb with 1 tablespoon of olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Make small incisions in the lamb and insert the garlic and rosemary into the incisions. Squeeze the lemon wedges over the lamb.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "knife, cutting board"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Roasting",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Place the lamb in a roasting pan and roast in the preheated oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes for medium-rare. Baste the lamb with the pan juices every 20 minutes.",
            "time": 75,
            "tool": "roasting pan, baster"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Resting",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Remove the lamb from the oven and let it rest for 10 minutes before carving.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "none"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 5,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Carve the lamb into slices and serve with your choice of sides.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "knife, serving platter"
        }
    ]
}
Serves_6:
{
    "recipeSource": "BBC Good Food",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-09-01",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Preheat the oven to 200¬∞C/180¬∞C fan/gas 6. Peel and chop the garlic cloves. Pick the leaves from the rosemary and thyme and chop them finely. Mix the garlic, rosemary, thyme, olive oil, salt and pepper together in a small bowl.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "oven, small bowl"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Preparing the Lamb",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Place the lamb in a roasting tin. Using a sharp knife, make small incisions all over the lamb. Rub the herb mixture all over the lamb, making sure to get it into the incisions. Cover the lamb with foil and leave to marinate for at least 30 minutes.",
            "time": 40,
            "tool": "roasting tin, foil, sharp knife"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking the Lamb",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Place the lamb in the preheated oven and roast for 1 hour 30 minutes for medium-rare, or until cooked to your liking. Baste the lamb with the juices from the roasting tin every 30 minutes. Remove the foil for the last 30 minutes of cooking to allow the lamb to brown.",
            "time": 90,
            "tool": "oven, roasting tin"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Resting and Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Remove the lamb from the oven and transfer it to a warm plate. Cover with foil and leave to rest for 15-20 minutes. Carve the lamb into slices and serve with your choice of vegetables and potatoes.",
            "time": 20,
            "tool": "plate, foil, carving knife"
        }
    ]
}

        {

        {

Serves_3:
{
    "recipeSource": "Vegan Kitchen",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-09-15",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Rinse and drain 1 can of kidney beans and 1 can of black beans. Chop 1 onion, 1 green bell pepper, and 2 cloves of garlic. Measure out 1 cup of long-grain rice.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "colander, knife, measuring cup"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "In a large pot, heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil over medium heat. Add the chopped onion, green bell pepper, and garlic. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add 1 teaspoon of paprika, 1 teaspoon of dried thyme, 1/2 teaspoon of cayenne pepper, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Stir to combine. Add the rinsed and drained beans, 1 can of diced tomatoes, and 2 cups of vegetable broth. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes.",
            "time": 30,
            "tool": "large pot"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "After 20 minutes, add the 1 cup of rice to the pot. Stir to combine. Cover the pot and simmer for an additional 20 minutes, or until the rice is cooked and the liquid has been absorbed.",
            "time": 20,
            "tool": "pot lid"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Fluff the rice with a fork and serve the jambalaya hot.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "fork"
        }
    ]
}

Serves_1:
{
    "recipeSource": "The Minimalist Baker",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-10-15",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Rinse 1/2 cup of lentils and soak them in water for at least 4 hours or overnight. Drain and rinse the lentils before using.",
            "time": 240,
            "tool": "bowl"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a pan over medium heat. Add 1/4 cup of chopped onion and 1 minced garlic clove and saut√© for 2-3 minutes until softened. Add 1/2 cup of chopped walnuts and cook for another 2-3 minutes until lightly toasted.",
            "time": 6,
            "tool": "pan"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add the soaked and drained lentils to the pan along with 1/2 cup of vegetable broth, 1/4 cup of tomato sauce, 1/2 teaspoon of dried oregano, 1/4 teaspoon of salt, and a pinch of black pepper. Stir to combine and bring to a simmer. Reduce the heat to low and let the mixture cook for 20-25 minutes until the lentils are tender and the sauce has thickened.",
            "time": 25,
            "tool": "pan"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Serve the walnut and lentil bolognese over your favorite pasta and garnish with fresh parsley or grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "plate"
        }
    ]
}
Serves_2:
{
    "recipeSource": "https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/walnut-lentil-bolognese",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-10-01",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Finely chop 1 onion, 2 garlic cloves, and 2 celery sticks. Grate 2 carrots. Drain and rinse 1 can of lentils. Roughly chop 100g of walnuts.",
            "time": 15,
            "tool": "chopping board, knife, grater"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large pan over medium heat. Add the chopped onion, garlic, and celery and cook for 5 minutes until softened. Add the grated carrot and cook for another 5 minutes. Add the chopped walnuts and cook for 2 minutes.",
            "time": 12,
            "tool": "large pan, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Simmering",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add 1 can of chopped tomatoes, 1 tablespoon of tomato puree, and 1 teaspoon of dried oregano to the pan. Stir well and bring to a simmer. Add the drained lentils and 100ml of vegetable stock. Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
            "time": 15,
            "tool": "large pan, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Serve the bolognese over cooked spaghetti or your favorite pasta. Garnish with fresh parsley and grated parmesan cheese, if desired.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "spoon, serving dish"
        }
    ]
}
Serves_4:
{
    "recipeSource": "The Spruce Eats",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-10-15",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Rinse 1 cup of lentils and soak them in water for 30 minutes. Finely chop 1 onion, 2 garlic cloves, and 2 celery stalks. Grate 1 carrot. Chop 1/2 cup of walnuts.",
            "time": 30,
            "tool": "bowl"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add the chopped onion, garlic, and celery and cook for 5 minutes until softened. Add the grated carrot and cook for another 2 minutes. Drain the soaked lentils and add them to the saucepan along with 1 can of chopped tomatoes, 1 tablespoon of tomato paste, 1 teaspoon of dried oregano, and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 20 minutes until the lentils are tender.",
            "time": 27,
            "tool": "saucepan"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Finishing",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Stir in the chopped walnuts and cook for another 5 minutes until the sauce has thickened. Serve over cooked pasta and garnish with fresh parsley and grated Parmesan cheese.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "saucepan"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Divide the pasta and sauce among 4 plates and serve immediately.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "plate"
        }
    ]
}

    "recipeSource": "Instant Pot Recipes",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-09-01",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Cut 2 lbs of pork shoulder into 2-inch cubes. Season with 1 tsp of salt, 1 tsp of cumin, 1 tsp of chili powder, and 1/2 tsp of black pepper. Peel and dice 1 onion and 4 cloves of garlic. Juice 2 oranges and 2 limes. Set aside.",
            "time": 15,
            "tool": "knife, cutting board, measuring spoons, citrus juicer"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Press the 'Saute' button on the Instant Pot. Add 1 tbsp of oil and wait until it's hot. Add the seasoned pork and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until browned on all sides. Add the diced onion and garlic and cook for another 2 minutes. Pour in the orange and lime juice and scrape the bottom of the pot to release any browned bits. Cancel the 'Saute' function.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "Instant Pot, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Pressure Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Close the lid of the Instant Pot and make sure the valve is set to 'Sealing'. Press the 'Manual' or 'Pressure Cook' button and set the timer for 30 minutes. Once the cooking cycle is complete, let the pressure release naturally for 10 minutes, then use the quick release to release any remaining pressure. Open the lid and use a slotted spoon to transfer the pork to a large bowl.",
            "time": 40,
            "tool": "Instant Pot, slotted spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Broiling",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Preheat the oven to broil. Line a baking sheet with foil. Use two forks to shred the pork into smaller pieces. Spread the pork in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet. Broil for 5-7 minutes, until crispy and browned. Serve hot with your favorite toppings, such as chopped cilantro, diced avocado, and lime wedges.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "oven, baking sheet, foil, forks"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 5,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Serve the carnitas hot with tortillas, rice, beans, and your favorite toppings.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "plates, utensils"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "recipeSource": "Allrecipes.com",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-09-01",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Trim excess fat from 2 lbs of beef chuck roast and cut into 2-inch cubes. Mince 4 cloves of garlic and 1 jalapeno pepper. Juice 2 limes. Combine beef, garlic, jalapeno, lime juice, 1 tbsp of ground cumin, 1 tbsp of dried oregano, 1 tsp of salt, and 1/2 tsp of black pepper in a large bowl. Mix well and let marinate for at least 30 minutes.",
            "time": 30,
            "tool": "large bowl"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Heat 1 tbsp of vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the beef mixture and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes. Transfer the beef to a slow cooker. Add 1/2 cup of beef broth to the skillet and scrape up any browned bits. Pour the broth into the slow cooker. Add 2 bay leaves and stir to combine.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "large skillet, slow cooker"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Slow Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Cover the slow cooker and cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 4 hours, until the beef is tender and falls apart easily.",
            "time": 240,
            "tool": "slow cooker"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Remove the bay leaves from the slow cooker. Using two forks, shred the beef into bite-sized pieces. Serve the barbacoa with warm tortillas, chopped cilantro, diced onions, and lime wedges.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "forks, tortillas, cilantro, onions, lime wedges"
        }
    ]
}

    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Peel and devein 1 pound of shrimp. Mince 3 cloves of garlic. Chop 1/4 cup of fresh parsley. Juice 1/2 lemon.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "knife, cutting board, juicer"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Add the shrimp and cook for 2-3 minutes per side until pink and cooked through. Remove the shrimp from the skillet and set aside.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "skillet"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Sauce",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add 2 tablespoons of butter to the skillet and melt. Add 1/4 cup of white wine and 1/4 teaspoon of red pepper flakes. Cook for 2-3 minutes until the sauce has reduced slightly. Add the cooked shrimp back to the skillet and toss to coat in the sauce.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "skillet"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Divide the shrimp scampi between two plates. Sprinkle with chopped parsley and drizzle with lemon juice. Serve immediately.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "plates"
        }
    ]
}

        {

{
    "recipeSource": "Allrecipes.com",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-09-01",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Peel and devein 1 pound of shrimp. Chop 1 onion, 1 green bell pepper, and 2 celery stalks. Mince 2 cloves of garlic.",
            "time": 15,
            "tool": "knife"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the chopped onion, bell pepper, and celery. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the minced garlic and cook for an additional 1 minute. Add 1 cup of long-grain white rice and stir to coat with the vegetables and oil. Add 1 can of diced tomatoes (undrained), 1 cup of chicken broth, 1 teaspoon of paprika, 1/2 teaspoon of dried thyme, and 1/4 teaspoon of cayenne pepper. Stir to combine. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and cover. Simmer for 20 minutes, or until the rice is tender and the liquid is absorbed.",
            "time": 30,
            "tool": "skillet"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Adding Shrimp",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add the peeled and deveined shrimp to the skillet. Stir to combine. Cover and cook for an additional 5 minutes, or until the shrimp are pink and cooked through.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "skillet"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh parsley if desired.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "plate"
        }
    ]
}

Serves_1:
{
    "recipeSource": "The Spruce Eats",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-10-15",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Prepare the Rice",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Rinse 1/2 cup of rice in cold water until the water runs clear. In a small saucepan, combine the rice with 3/4 cup of water and 1/4 cup of coconut milk. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and cover. Cook for 18-20 minutes, or until the rice is tender and the liquid has been absorbed.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "small saucepan"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Prepare the Tofu",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Cut 100g of firm tofu into bite-sized cubes. In a small bowl, mix together 1/2 teaspoon of five spice powder, 1/4 teaspoon of salt, and a pinch of black pepper. Toss the tofu in the spice mixture until evenly coated.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "small bowl"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Cook the Tofu",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a non-stick pan over medium-high heat. Add the tofu and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side, or until golden brown and crispy.",
            "time": 6,
            "tool": "non-stick pan"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Finish the Rice",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Once the rice is cooked, remove it from the heat and let it sit for 5 minutes. Fluff the rice with a fork, then stir in 1/4 cup of coconut milk and a pinch of salt.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "fork"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 5,
            "stageTitle": "Serve",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Divide the rice between two bowls and top with the crispy tofu. Enjoy!",
            "time": 2,
            "tool": "bowls"
        }
    ]
}

            "time": 25,
            "tool": "medium saucepan"
        },
        {

            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Cut 8 ounces of firm tofu into 1-inch cubes. In a small bowl, whisk together 1 tablespoon of soy sauce, 1 tablespoon of hoisin sauce, and 1/2 teaspoon of Chinese five spice powder. Add the tofu to the bowl and toss to coat.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "small bowl"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Cook the Tofu",

        {

            "time": 10,
            "tool": "large nonstick skillet"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Make the Sauce",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "In a small saucepan, combine 1 can of coconut milk, 2 tablespoons of soy sauce, 1 tablespoon of honey, 1 tablespoon of rice vinegar, and 1 teaspoon of five spice powder. Bring to a simmer over medium heat and cook for 5-7 minutes, or until the sauce has thickened slightly.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "small saucepan"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 5,
            "stageTitle": "Combine and Serve",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Add the cooked tofu to the skillet with the sauce and toss to coat. Serve the tofu over the coconut rice and garnish with chopped cilantro and sliced green onions.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "skillet"
        }
    ]
}

        {

            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Preheat the air fryer to 400¬∞F (200¬∞C).",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "Air fryer"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Marinating the Chicken",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "In a bowl, mix together 1 pound (450g) of chicken breast, 1 tablespoon of soy sauce, 1 tablespoon of rice vinegar, 1 tablespoon of cornstarch, and 1 teaspoon of sesame oil. Let it marinate for 10 minutes.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "Bowl"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking the Chicken",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Place the marinated chicken in the air fryer basket and cook for 10-12 minutes, flipping halfway through, until the chicken is cooked through and crispy.",
            "time": 12,
            "tool": "Air fryer"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Making the Sauce",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "In a small saucepan, mix together 1/4 cup (60ml) of chicken broth, 2 tablespoons of soy sauce, 2 tablespoons of hoisin sauce, 1 tablespoon of rice vinegar, 1 tablespoon of honey, 1 teaspoon of sesame oil, and 1/2 teaspoon of red pepper flakes. Bring to a boil and let it simmer for 2-3 minutes until the sauce thickens.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "Saucepan"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 5,
            "stageTitle": "Coating the Chicken",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "In a bowl, mix together the cooked chicken and the sauce until the chicken is coated evenly.",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "Bowl"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 6,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Serve the General Tso air fryer chicken with steamed rice and garnish with sliced green onions and sesame seeds.",
            "time": 0,
            "tool": "Plate"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "recipeSource": "Allrecipes.com",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-11-15",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Preheat the oven to 375¬∞F (190¬∞C).",
            "time": 5,
            "tool": "oven"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Cook 12 lasagna noodles according to package directions.",
            "time": 20,
            "tool": "stove"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "In a large skillet, cook 1 pound (450g) ground turkey over medium heat until browned. Drain any excess fat.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "skillet"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Add 1 jar (24 ounces/680g) of your favorite pasta sauce to the skillet with the turkey. Simmer for 10 minutes.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "skillet"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 5,
            "stageTitle": "Assembly",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "In a 9x13 inch (23x33 cm) baking dish, spread a thin layer of the turkey sauce on the bottom. Place 4 lasagna noodles on top of the sauce. Spread 1/3 of the remaining sauce over the noodles. Sprinkle 1 cup (100g) of shredded mozzarella cheese over the sauce.",
            "time": 15,
            "tool": "baking dish"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 6,
            "stageTitle": "Assembly",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Repeat the layering process with 4 more lasagna noodles, 1/3 of the sauce, and 1 cup (100g) of shredded mozzarella cheese.",
            "time": 15,
            "tool": "baking dish"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 7,
            "stageTitle": "Assembly",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Add the final layer of 4 lasagna noodles, the remaining sauce, and 1 cup (100g) of shredded mozzarella cheese.",
            "time": 15,
            "tool": "baking dish"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 8,
            "stageTitle": "Baking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Cover the baking dish with foil and bake for 25 minutes. Remove the foil and bake for an additional 25 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.",
            "time": 50,
            "tool": "oven"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 9,
            "stageTitle": "Serving",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Let the lasagna cool for 10 minutes before slicing and serving.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "knife"
        }
    ]
}

Serves_5:
{
    "recipeSource": "Allrecipes.com",
    "lastUpdated": "2021-10-15",
    "instructions": [
        {
            "stepNumber": 1,
            "stageTitle": "Preparation",
            "stepType": "prep",
            "instruction": "Chop 1 onion and 3 cloves of garlic. Slice 500g of turkey breast into thin strips. Measure out 500g of pasta. Rinse and chop 200g of spinach.",
            "time": 10,
            "tool": "knife, cutting board, measuring cup"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 2,
            "stageTitle": "Cooking",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "In a large pot, heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil over medium heat. Add the chopped onion and garlic and cook until softened, about 3 minutes. Add the sliced turkey and cook until browned, about 5 minutes. Add 1 can of diced tomatoes, 500g of pasta, 1 teaspoon of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of black pepper, and 1 teaspoon of dried oregano. Stir to combine.",
            "time": 15,
            "tool": "large pot, wooden spoon"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 3,
            "stageTitle": "Simmering",
            "stepType": "cook",
            "instruction": "Add enough water to the pot to cover the pasta. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer for 10-12 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the pasta is cooked and the sauce has thickened.",
            "time": 12,
            "tool": "none"
        },
        {
            "stepNumber": 4,
            "stageTitle": "Finishing",
            "stepType": "serve",
            "instruction": "Stir in the chopped spinach and cook for an additional 2-3 minutes until wilted. Serve hot, garnished with grated Parmesan cheese if desired.",
            "time": 3,
            "tool": "none"
        }
    ]
}
